New Jersey Transit Trains Are Delayed Up to 45 Minutes for Signal Problems

-- B y   S t e f a n i e   B a t c h o - L i n o
-- 
2011-06-17T19:51:24Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-17/new-jersey-transit-trains-are-delayed-up-to-45-minutes-for-signal-problems.html
New Jersey Transit  said trains in
and out of  New York City  are subject to delays of 30 to 45
minutes due to weather-related signal problems. The information
was disclosed in an e-mailed statement. Earlier the NJ Transit
said delays were as much as 30 minutes.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stefanie Batcho-Lino at 
 sbatcholino1@bloomberg.net  